				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Camping for Dessicated Halfling Mask<a name="17643"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 28 04 1:37 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>it does exist... though it is a rare and exotic beast.
<br />

<br />
spawn rate is about 29%
<br />
spawn time is 19 minutes
<br />
pher's and named do not walk from spawn point unless you move them (aggro) or kill too slow (nuke and his hp drop to 2% instead of dead). when he walks, ~everything~ aggros
<br />
veteran and named enrage at 9 percent
<br />

<br />
65 bard with 60 druid buffs could almost always melee any down without heals.
<br />

<br />
over 11 days...
<br />
230 mobs:
<br />
110 veterans
<br />
  54 scarred
<br />
66 named - 18 rings, 14 capes, 33 backstabbers
<br />
and 1 mask
<br />

<br />
also nice spells and research components, i made a decent amount of exp and cash just killing the pher/named. took me from max ally to apprehensive.
<br />

<br />
met a bard who would charm the PHer and sic it down the hall past the chokidai, using FM when charm broke, letting him walk back up the hall, then resending it down till it poofed. no faction hit, no exp, no loot, but faster than meleeing. 
<br />

<br />
if you're communicating, you can easily lull down a fast moving pair/small group.  i personally lived in droga for a bunch of gear/exp/cash, thus i had no issues with the faction.</span></td>
