				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Camping for Dessicated Halfling Mask<a name="17816"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 29 04 1:25 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>When i camped my mask, i just took a friend and fought my way down to the camp site. we were both 60+ so it wasn't hard at all. I've tried to lull the mobs all the way down to the camp but their agro range is decievingly big and there are a bunch that hide around corners that you'd need an ss helm to lull them before they catch your sent. 
<br />

<br />
It took me 1 week of continuous camping with countless PH's and named to get it. I think it ranks up in my top 10 for most memorable moments in the game. The camp is boring and you have to be one stubborn SOB to camp it. 
<br />

<br />
All i did was place myself on the wall out of agro range in between the PH/named spawn postion and the mob on the wall directly opposite of the undead miners. charm the mob on the wall, pull the ph/named towards you so you have a little more room to play with and sick your pet on him. Depending on which mob happened to spawn as your pet, I'd land a slow on ph/named so he wouldn't chew threw my pet to fast. usually it would take 2 charms to ensure that both mobs were around the 15% mark or my pet would die. watch out though, after you get around 10% they like to run so you want your snare working for you.  Kill the ph/named  (he should almost be running by this point) and wait for the next spawn time. Its very straight forward but i'd suggest having FM as a get out of jail free card and have a gate potion handy. You don't want to be having to trek outa there after you get your mask, trust me....you'll just want to go show it off as quickly as possible :p
<br />

<br />

<br />
Rooben</span></td>
